LAGOS – Former governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Lagos state, Jimi Agbaje has advised President Muhammadu Buhari to make security and the revamping of the economy his top priorities in 2022. Speaking with Daily Independent, Agbaje also urged the president amendments that will make Nigeria’s constitution more federal in structure, such as the electoral act bill which includes electronic transmission of results. He said ” I expect Mr President to pass amendments that will make our constitution more federal in structure and the electoral law including electronic transmission of results. Says Ortom Had No Hand In Selection Of Ochi’Idoma -CPS 2023: APC Working On One Lie That Will Return PDP To Power… He should also make security and economy top priorities”. The President, in his New Year message, had said Nigerians should expect new jobs in 2022. He also said his administration would deploy ICT (Information and Communications Technology) platforms for the purpose of job creation and also ensure the diversification of the economy to support other emerging sectors. On the security challenge, he promised that government would not relent in tackling the problem citing the “number of insurgents and bandits who have willingly surrendered to our security forces and continue to do so through various channels and the Safe Corridor created for that purpose.” On the economy, Buhari said the 4.03% growth in Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in the third quarter of 2021 is indicative of the recovery being recorded in the economy and the confidence that is being shown through the policies the government has put in place after the outbreak of the pandemic.